{"type":"message","id":"853d0a53","parentId":"09cd5c02","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:23:44.137Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ajy3f9lwo3nv_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5068\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3156\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[master c48e705] pulse: 2026-03-24 112315\n 6 files changed, 330 insertions(+), 78 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 112315.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 112315.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 112215.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 112315 - CFI analysis revealed that 94.3% of frequency-invariants have CFI<0.7, meaning frequency-based compression mostly captures metaprogramming artifacts (process noise) rather than actual research trajectory. The experiment design exists but needs implementation.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"clear-ember","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5068\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3156\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[master c48e705] pulse: 2026-03-24 112315\n 6 files changed, 330 insertions(+), 78 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 112315.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 112315.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 112215.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 112315 - CFI analysis revealed that 94.3% of frequency-invariants have CFI<0.7, meaning frequency-based compression mostly captures metaprogramming artifacts (process noise) rather than actual research trajectory. The experiment design exists but needs implementation.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774365824133}}
{"type":"message","id":"d7154095","parentId":"853d0a53","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:23:44.142Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ajy3f9lwo3nv_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 112215\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action that advances the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent status:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n- CFI Analysis is done with key findings about frequency-invariants\r\n- Next pending action: CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\r\n\r\nThe pending action is to implement a CFI-weighted compression experiment. This would involve:\r\n1. Creating a compression method that weights tokens/features by their CFI scores\r\n2. Comparing prediction accuracy vs the frequency baseline\r\n\r\nLet me check what's in the research directory to understand the current state better.\r\n\r\nI should create an experiment file that:\r\n1. Takes the CFI results from CFI_RESULTS.md\r\n2. Designs a compression experiment comparing CFI-weighted vs frequency-based approaches\r\n3. Sets up the methodology for comparing next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThis advances the pending goal \"CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\"\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis revealed that 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0) while only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7). The next logical step is to implement the pending CFI-weighted compression experiment to validate whether CFI-based filtering outperforms frequency-based baseline.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a comprehensive experiment design for CFI-weighted compression, specifying methodology to compare CFI-filtered vs frequency-baseline next-pulse prediction using the existing pulse history data.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24  \r\n**Status:** Design Phase\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression will outperform frequency-only baseline for next-pulse prediction because it filters out metaprogramming artifacts (CFI=0) while preserving causal research trajectory signals (CFI>0.7).\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Dataset\r\n- Source: `research/pulse_*.md` history files\r\n- Ground truth: Full text of each pulse\r\n- Compression target: Predict next pulse content\r\n\r\n### Conditions (3-way comparison)\r\n\r\n| Condition | Method | Keep Criteria |\r\n|-----------|--------|---------------|\r\n| Baseline | Frequency-only | top-N by frequency |\r\n| CFI-Weighted | CFI scores | CFI > threshold |\r\n| Hybrid | Frequency × CFI | Combined score > threshold |\r\n\r\n### Metrics\r\n1. **Compression ratio** (% of original tokens retained)\r\n2. **Next-pulse prediction accuracy** (BLEU/ROUGE vs actual next pulse)\r\n3. **Causal signal preservation** (% of high-CFI invariants retained)\r\n\r\n### Implementation Steps\r\n\r\n1. **Extract invariants** from pulse history using n-gram frequency analysis\r\n2. **Compute CFI** for each invariant (already have methodology in CFI_RESULTS.md)\r\n3. **Build three compression models:**\r\n   - `compression/baseline_freq.py` - frequency ranking\r\n   - `compression/cfi_filter.py` - CFI threshold filtering\r\n   - `compression/hybrid_score.py` - freq × CFI product\r\n4. **Evaluate** each on held-out pulse pairs\r\n5. **Report** which condition best predicts next pulse content\r\n\r\n### Expected Outcome\r\n- CFI filter will remove ~45% of invariants (noise) with minimal prediction loss\r\n- Hybrid condition likely optimal: retains signal while filtering noise\r\n- Baseline frequency-only wastes capacity on metaprogramming artifacts\r\n\r\n## Files to Create\r\n- `compression/experiment_runner.py` - main experiment loop\r\n- `compression/invariant_extractor.py` - n-gram frequency analysis\r\n- `compression/cfi_calculator.py` - CFI computation for invariants\r\n- `compression/models/` - three compression model implementations\r\n- `compression/results.md` - experiment output\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 11:22:39\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774365824137}}
